%N A319812 Square array read by antidiagonals: T(n,k) = (1 + i)-adic valuation of n + k*i, n >= 0, k >= 0, or -1 if n + k*i = 0.
%C A319812 Equivalently, T(n,k) = 2-adic valuation of n^2 + k^2.
%C A319812 Table is symmetric with respect to the main diagonal. For any Gaussian integer z = x + y*i, its (1 + i)-adic valuation is T(|x|,|y|) if z != 0 and +oo if z = 0.
%F A319812 For n + k*i != 0:
%F A319812 T(n,k) = v(n^2 + k^2, 2) where v(k, 2) = A007814(k) is the 2-adic valuation of k.
%F A319812 T(n,k) = 2*min{v(n, 2), v(k, 2)} if v(n, 2) != v(k, 2), otherwise v(n, 2) + v(k, 2) + 1. Here v(0, 2) = +oo.
